commitResults.messageTitle: Change some stuff to test CI

commitResults.messageBody:
UI needs space to have a meetings dashboard.

This would be useful to view reminders and meetings, or group tags.

Lets-

Use BorderPane Layout to get the rough skeletal UI ready. The meetings dashboard will be inserted in after meetings functionality is merged with this branch.

We do not have a GUI display for meetings.

This makes it difficult for users to have visual information about the list of meetings scheduled

Lets-
- Implement a barebones implementation of the GUI
- A Meeting dashboard that stores a ListView to all meetings ( similar to PersonListView implementation)
- display for each meeting a MeetingCard with information of the Meetings.

NOTE:
- I have minimally decorated it, feel welcome to add in your own style classes.
- Due to unable to fetch meetings from model at this point in time, I
 have randomly inputted in a few custom meetings to the ListView inside
MainWindow # fillInnerParts function. Can delete these after the model for meetings
is implemented
Needed in order to pass CI.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add API to convert Meetings into Json
commitResults.messageBody:
We need to store the meetings.

In order to store the data on meetings into json, we need to convert the classes into a more
jackson - friendly  version. Therefore it is necessary to make the class and its API.

Lets-
Make a JsonAdaptedMeeting class with conversion API
Fix checkstyle errors on some fxml files.

The ordering of the import statements is wrong.

Therefore rerodering is required to pass checkstyle

As a user, I would like to display profile images beside the person details in the addressbook

This is so that I can personalise and remember my contacts better. Some of the contacts would be using wordpress accounts
or have online avatars. I would want these contacts profiles to be automatically loaded. If there is a connection error, it should display an empty profiile picture.

Lets-
Add functionality to load the images from web using the Gravatar API

NOTE-
Slight implementation details to note as well as future directions
- Loading times take a while as connecting to the url takes some time
- May need to implement caching
- May need to set default profile picture and pass the choice to user in USER_PREFS in case connection fails
- May need to touch up GUI
